Privacy Policy for Simple URL Replacer
Effective date: February 21, 2026

Simple URL Replacer respects your privacy.

1. Data We Collect
We do not collect personal data, account data, or browsing history on external servers.

The extension stores only the following settings locally on your device using chrome.storage.local:

URL template
Replace token
2. How We Use Data
Stored settings are used only to:

Build a new URL from your template and selected/input text
Open the generated URL in a new browser tab
3. Data Sharing
We do not sell, share, or transfer your data to third parties.

4. Permissions
The extension uses these permissions only for core functionality:

storage: save extension settings locally
contextMenus: add right-click menu action
tabs: open generated URL in a new tab
activeTab: access current tab after user action
scripting: show input prompt when no text is selected
5. Data Retention
All extension data remains on your local device until you clear it or uninstall the extension.

6. Security
No remote database or cloud service is used by this extension.

7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. Updates will be reflected by changing the effective date.

